VimNuke

send python code to Nuke from vim

Requirements: 

- Vim with python support
- The Foundry Nuke (tested with version 6.3v4 - Linux_64bits)

Nuke Setup:

- start commandPort: 
	from commandPort import server
	server.start()

- stop commandPort:

	import threading
	for t in threading.enumerate():
    	# print t.getName()
    	if t.getName() == 'commandPort':
        	t.stop()

Vim Setup:

Manual:
Copy plugin and doc directories into your '.vim' directory

Pathogen:

Just clone this repository into a subdirectory of your `.vim/bundle` directory like so:

cd ~/.vim/bundle
git clone https://bitbucket.org/sydh/vimnuke.git

Vundle:

Add the following line to your .vimrc:

Bundle 'https://bitbucket.org/sydh/vimnuke.git'

and run :BundleInstall in vim.

Usage:

The default mappings to toggle the plugin is 
- '<leader>sn' : send selection or whole buffer if no selection
- '<leader>sN' : send whole buffer even if something is selected

Help:
- vim : help vimNuke

Known bugs/limitations:
- Localhost nuke only 
